\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did she do any party work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 She? No, no. No, but when I was - when
 I was twenty - when I was twenty-one - you still - it was only householders that had the vote. But I managed to get a lodger's vote - a lodger vote - could have a vote. The parties used to work one - one with the other, and - view the room, you see, I ha
d a room to myself at that time because my brother had died, and I had the - the room to myself, the bedroom, so that qualified me for a vote. So that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 As a lodger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I - no, I was the lodger. I got the lodger's - I was a lodger you see. I got - I
'd got a room to myself, so that qualified me, so the day I became twenty-one I put in for my lodger's vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you think in general that men voted as their employers did because they were scared of losing their jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well - the - form the - in
dustrial revolution on of course - the - the - I think - I've always thought and I believe there's a lot of ground for the belief, my - my friend Doctor Dony is the - with regard to the - industrial revolution right up to now, he gives - he's given lectur
e
s, any amount of lectures - on the political issues over the years. And there's no doubt about it, that - trades unionism - coming into - being gradually from the industrial revolution time, from the Tolpuddle Martyrs on - alienated men from the churches,
 you follow, and they gradually went left, hence the Liberal party building up. Largely. Because - the Liberal party at the turn of the century was far more socialistic - than the Labour party today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You don't remember a time when the men would have voted automatically as their employers expected them to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh - no, not - not in this district anyway. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I don't suppose your parents had much time apart from work but did they have any hobbies or things they did in their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, the
y had no time for that, you see. You see, for a - for men it was a sixty hour week. Invariably a sixty hour week, could be more. I mean I worked sixty hours a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did she belong to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
No. There wouldn't be much - there wouldn't be - there wouldn't be much activity on the part of the - ordinary sort of working class - mother. Outside her home, she wouldn't have - she wouldn't have the - time - what with looking after fami
ly, see, washing and all those sort of activities in the home - kept her busy. In the main - I - I - those in - in - enjoying better circumstances - would of course - be attached largely to the churches, doing different sorts of things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were either of your fathers interested in sport, racing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
The one - my - my own father - yes, my own father was interested in the - in horses, not for racing, but for traveling around with them. He was friendly with the - the hors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 
e trainer at the local - Marque}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
s of Bute, then he went - he - he - he went to Rumania and became - a trained or the then Royal Family' of Rumania - and - and he came into Germany, one of those - those states at that time, one of the - German states, but my father was very fond of ho
rses. My step-father was fond of football, but - but he didn't have much time really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember them belonging to any savings clubs, for shoes or sickness or funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 There was a sickness - you see be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 ore the national health of course - 
one paid the doctor's bill if one could. And there's no doubt about any men - man - amount of people died - because they couldn't afford a doctor. Must have done. But - in - in the local - in the local town here - there was a medical institute formed - by
 
- a society - similar to - the national deposit society and so on, got together and they formed a national deposit - this - medical institute - with about four doctors employed, and - the large membership paid a few coppers a week, and that qualified you 
for medical attention.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Your parents did that did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No. No, that was - later on. But in my early days - in my early days people doing it but she never did. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I think you said you started school at three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, 1892.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Can you remember going to school your first day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Yes. Definitely, I can remember the first day at school - with - I can remember the - there were three or four ladies who were taking their - youngsters too, to this infants school. I've been in the room sin
ce lecturing on the hat trade, it was rather queer, but - I can remember - I - I can visualize the women in their - sort of - aprons, the long bodies above me as a small child, you follow. And I remember these ladies frocks as I must have come past in bet
w
een them somehow, seeing - these long frocks and - perhaps aprons, I forget now, one of which must have been my mother, and then the - someone taking me up to the form where I had to sit, they were just forms then, there were no - no chairs or anything, i
t was just - backless forms. And - sitting in the form and - my - curls hanging onto the shoulder which was customary those days, boys had curls. The boy at the back of me pulling my hair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were you miserable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Then a - a few - a little later on, t
he next year I - the infants school was in the same - next to the building of the - the - more adult - girls school. And four or five of these girls running around a corner knocked me over, broke my arm. And I - I broke it later on in the same - in the sa
me school but - broke my arm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were boys and girls separated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 In the school yes. In - in the - in the - later on. In the infants no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What time did you start in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 School, nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And come home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Come - coming home to lunch - at twelve, then back I think at half past one or quarter to two if I remember. And then - until four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have far to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I didn't, no - about - not above ten minutes walk - normally for an adult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you go with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
In the early days. Mother - mother - I remember, used to take me - or - a neighbour, you see, she'd got - at that time she'd got - I was the youngest, that's right, yes, I remember her taking me or the woman next - the lady next 
door taking me to school. But of course there was hardly any traffic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What did you think of school, do you remember, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, I had one big fear, I used to be - I used to faint at blood and - yes, I fainted at blood right through my 
life until about ten years ago. Even red ink - even red ink. I remember the - go - going up to the - up to the - headmistress, and - asking - she was asking my name and then taking it down on the register and I saw the red ink and - off I went. I think - 
it seemed to be rather - common in those days for children to faint at blood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you like learning, did you like the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I liked - yes, some I did, but there was more discipline. Although my - this schoolmaster friend you see who wrote the
 books, he - he was a school - grammar school master, and he was also a master of a - a school of - during the war at Kentish Town, and - he used to talk about discipline, and his school was evacuated to - Manton near - in - Rutlandshire, into a little vi
l
lage, and - I noticed there the - the children - I went up with him - because he was take away from Manton because he had been a qualified engineer. Was forced into the London Polytechnic to teach engineering. So - we went up to see this school where he'd
 
been a master, I remember all the children, the London School here the Doc Dony as he was called - they were crowding at the railway station to meet him, and - but there was discipline even in that school, in that - village school, that's quite discipline
.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have one teacher that taught you everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
No. Ah I'm sorry. Yes. Yes. But except - yes, it's quite true, there was - you see as the forms - as you qualified the next form was a teacher of the next year, you follow, and again -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were they all women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Men in - men in the boys school, women in the girls school. There was no women in the boys schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Was there any punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Cane. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What did you get the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh any - insubordination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Yes, lots of times, yes. As a matter of fact we feared - in that - in that book that you've got - there's a - there's a photo of - my school, with - there was a sort of a high - there was a - there was - Wa
ll Street High Grade School which was a little more educational with qualifications than the normal board school. And the top boy - top form boys from the board schools graduated to that - that school. And the schoolmaster was a very stern strict man, he 
was then the president of the PSA, Pleasant Sunday Afternoons Men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
s - school, which - then we got about - well if I remember about two hundred men. So you see well they've all gone can't you. Got cars and so on. But - he got - he'd got a very deep frown and we were always frightened of the frown, let alone the stick.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did the girls get the stick as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Not so much. But there was the cane, they was more disciplined. Oh we daren't - we daren't do - as - as for playing truant, you daren't do that. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were your parents interested in your school work, was your mother interested in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Yes. Yes. But of course - as I say, that - one only - tried to get on to leave school and earn - in order to earn money you see, I was earning - when I le
ft - when I left school I had been earning half a crown a week, suddenly I went to five shillings. So it was quite big you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember if the teachers had favourites in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. They did. Oh yes, they were - yes, they had favourites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What sort of children were favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well so far as I remember they were - the favourites usually were - favourites from those of the better off - parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were there gangs in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Pardon? There was - it was rather quee
r - I - I don't remember gangs in the schools so much but there were gangs - there were gangs in the - in the - in the - in the towns - gangs between streets, streets, for instance I remember we - we used to walk - war - we used to war against New Town St
reet and Chase Street, the boys of - of the Streets a little lower down, they used to come up and - we used to - have - sham fights and so on. But there was nothing very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How did you get on with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well this - my - my two sisters - d
ied before - when they were - quite young you see, seven or eight years of age, my two own sisters. Then my brother - he was older than me, by about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were you good friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes. I - I thought a great deal of my brother, tremend
ous - tremendously. I copied him in many ways. Until he died. And then - as he died from - the same - trouble as the two sisters and my father, heart disease, I became very ner - nervous and frightened, do you follow - because - it was generally agreed th
a
t I was due to die. And so - the things that he did, the exertions he smoked a little, so I - I didn't smoke until I was twenty-six. And I avoided the exertions of swimming and - and those sort of hard exertions, well hardest ones, but - I got on wonderfu
lly well with him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 When you were small did you play with other children in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Oh yes. Oh - the streets of course the - streets were composed almost everywhere - of the - the - houses coming up to the pavements, do you follow, and the - 
long pavements down the streets, well - there were the competitions with - the tops, racing - racing each other, up one side of the street then crossing over the road and - race down the other. Oftentimes there was a good deal of - fraud you know, kicking
 your top - on the quite and so on, but those - those sort of - hop -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How did you push the top along, with a stick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, with a - a whip. Whip, yes. You spun it - you kept - you - you spun your top and then - yes, there was quite a little art - a
ttached to it. Then there was the games of hopscotch wasn't there and - hopscotch was quite a - a - quite a - that's right, yes, then on one leg you see. And all sorts of funny little games such as that. But - with regard to the boys - there were the wars
 between the streets. Rushing round with - sticks and so on. Not too - not too violent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 None got hurt did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Pardon? Oh some - some did occasionally but it - that was more fun that anything. But - a - a war would be a - arranged between so and
 so street, a few streets off and your own particular street. We used to - we used to have a war with the - war - wars with a street named {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Chase Street{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, quite a - quite a - a famous street in - street in the town at that time. Very poor street you know. Po
or little urchins, much poorer than our particular neighbourhood. But - we had a way - we had a way of - going over - various - walls and so on, creeping - through trees and so on to avoid them and then catch them and - and catch them from the back way, d
o
 you follow. All sorts of little games like that. There was - lots of games at night time of course in - in the winter time - 'course it's a mistake to - to imagine that all winters were - icy winters but - when one looks back one thinks that they were, b
u
t they weren't you know, really, because - there was quite a - a prominent man gave a history of Luton the other year - William Janes, one of the - old Lutonians, he's about - seven or eight years my senior, still lives, but he gave a - his experiences an
d knowledge of Luton those many years ago. And he sad about the hot summers, you know, the hot summers, always the hot summers, never wet. Or at least he - he por - portrayed {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
 never wet. Well - 1907, that was the wettest summer then on record and I thi
nk it's not quite been beaten since. I was making the straw helmets for the - the - the straw helmets for the police straw helmets in that book isn't there? Well I made those helmets, those particular helmets. That time I was making for the firm who made 
-
 patented the helmets you see, and I carried on after the - the proprietor died I carried on the business until 1915 when - we closed down, but I blocked those particular helmets, that was in 1911, the - 1911 - election at that time. But Janes - mentioned
 
about the hot summers, and about the police helmets, but well of course really they - they weren't necessary really. Or - they - they were necessary, they wouldn't be necessary today, because of our wet summers. Then I - I - I simply - wrote an article fo
r the Bedfordshire magazine - describing the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
 of my young days, which is very similar to his, only that the weather was different you see. And I said that - the - the photo - a photo had been produced of the whole of the Luton police force supplied wit
h these - straw helmets, after two summers wear - one the - wettest summer on record, and they were still - lovely helmets you see. So it - it's surprising that lots of things -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What did you do to make them strong enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well they was tightly 
- they were - plaited - well, I could show you how to plait - plait them if I got - if I got the straw here. Then they were stiffened with gelatine stiffen - stiffening. Very hard. And then eventually they were - the - the - the stickyness of the - surfac
e
 was got rid of, by what we used to call sweating. That was putting hot - cloths over - wet cloths and that took the - the - in a heated pan, in a hot mould the same - same - shape as the helmet, and that would take the - the surface - of the gelatine awa
y. Then we used to - then - treat them with glycerine. But they were still very very hard, like these - Salvation Army bonnets, they were still as hard as a brick, I blocked the last one myself - last - last year, this last year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How long did those police helmets last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Police helmets, two summers. Two summers wear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How long did police go on wearing them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 The Police? Oh they - they stopped wearing in between the two wars but when we closed down, when we closed down another firm later on 
after the first world war started making them again. And - but they - I - they didn't make them so strong, the plait wasn't so strong, it wasn't the local plait made from the plait - the wheat straw in the district then plaited by the women who were in th
e villages. It was - plaits - a plait done in - made in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}China{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. It wasn't nearly so strong. So - it - they went on until the boater - the straw boater, the bowler, and - those sort of hats went out when the car came in. You follow? When the motor car came in
 gradually - somehow the boater went out. The boater was the hat that used to blow off quite easily. But - meantime of course we made - we made the hat - of this wheat straw for King Edward VII and Prince Christian, our firm, and - for - shooting in Bavar
ia - shooting - sort of - these boars you know, and - it - those - those hats were copied gradually by - we made one for Whitelaw Read who was a - American ambassador down at - \{BLANK\}
 A.J. Balfour, Lord Balfour eventually and - lots of those people. They'r
e the high sort of people used to buy these hats, and then Dunns, you read - the Dunns, same Dunns - started to order them for ordinary wear, and suddenly there was swamped, and other manufacturers started to copy the idea, if you follow. Then the ordinar
y little - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bute{\*\xmlclose}
 brim, instead of that E - Anthony Eden rolled brim which was - the original hat that we made for - King Edward - the - the soft brim - really replaced that more - ostentatious sort of hat. And that - that soft trilby as they were called - re
ally beat the boater and the bowler. I know the bowler was still worn by the - the - the - more or less businessmen but - gradually speaking it went out of fashion. And of course, the trilby knocked the cap out you see. Up until that time dear - you could
 tell - you could tell a man's station as I said the other week, you could tell his station in life by his dress, especially his hat. 'Cos the high silk hat, used to make the high silk hat in straw too for - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Ascot
{\*\xmlclose} and so on. And I made some of them, I still - one of my hats in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
 museum on show. Used to make this very very fine straw - the - the shape of the high silk hat, very difficult to make but - used to make quite a lot of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Going back to the games you used to play did the boys and the girls play together or were they separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
The girls - well the girls were skipping you see, skipping was very very popular - little pastime again. Nobody - they used to play with tops of course, but not hopscotch - on the pavement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That was boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
That was boys and girls but chiefly girls. Chiefly girls, the boys - had the more little rough game - mind you they played football a lot - in the street. Kicking anything about. Football was very popular. I - I played - played football
 when I was - eight or nine, I remember playing goal keeper and we lost thirteen nil. Ah but then I - I believe I've told you that coming up the - the London Road - the steep hill going up towards London from Luton - we left off the game - around to the s
ide - the verge of the road which is now all houses of course, to watch this - first car come - up the hill. The first car in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
. Became a famous car eventually. Sometimes it got up you see and it did this particular day. So that was - of course the - the -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Great excitement was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Yes, it - it was quite excite - the - that - that car - the Langley car was - a high car, and - yes, they used to get up - they used to get up at the back of the car, similar to the old brake and the wagonettes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 The door at the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's right, yes. So that was the first car, then eventually - I can remember just the one taxi, just one taxi in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}. And motor cars were very very rare of course in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 When you were playing and you got dirty would your mother mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
No, no, mothers didn't mind much, it was the sort of thing - as a matter of fact I've been - I've been out this morning - and it - it - brought my - memories back to those old days. Been out with a friend of mine who 
- who was hat manufacturer, I've been doing some work - hat work this morning, and we went out to collect some hats - a lot of it - a lot of hats are trimmed round the villages. Do you follow? Or near - near the estates, this was on an estate. About two m
iles out from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
 here. And - we - went to this - council house - and there seemed to be a lot - I - I've not been before, went into the house, and - the place seemed filled up - with children, and I said - I thought - gosh, there must be several - people
s children here, so I said to the lady - what a lot of children, how many are there? She says, eight. So I said, eight. Well where do they all come from? She says, me. Me. Well that's very rare isn't it? Yes, there was eight and - they - they seemed to be
 
- from about - oh I don't know - not quite two years old, and the top one must have been about - ten or eleven, not more. It did seem - I might be wrong but it - the little girl didn't seem more than - about eleven, but - they were all more or less at hom
e. Well of course that was usual in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you spend a lot of time out in the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes. Oh yes, oh - yes. There - there wasn't enough room - room in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you play late at night in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Sometimes. Yes - o
ne of the - I'm afraid I shall rather shock you but one of the - one of the sights of that - that - particular time was to see the fights - that happened between - the public houses when the men came out drunk. And drunkenness was very rife, as you can up
 - I don't know whether you - would know that but - drunkenness was - was very rife in those days. And it was - quite a sight to see these - these fights.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You kids liked to watch them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes, went down purposely. Then sledging of course
, sledging in the winter time, or sleighing, whatever you like to - like to - to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Where did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 We used to make our - make the - or the fathers used to make the sledges, round - any - round the hills round the - in the villages 
and the towns, at - used to - sledge quite a lot in Luton here, down the - these -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 There's a lot of hills around {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose} aren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's right. And then the skating the ponds. The ponds - lots of youngsters skated, I did, I skated when I was 
about - nine, I could do the outside edge and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Wouldn't skates have been rather expensive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 ll - as regards myself - I - in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 herited a pair of skates from my father who had died, and he'd - he'd had them - given to him by - a - a friend of his, 
who had won the - the Lancashire - the Fenn - the Fenn, there was a Fenn competition every year. Rather shows you doesn't it - that it was a yearly competition, skating. Whether it - whether some years I didn't happen I don't know, but - it was generally 
accepted that - the Fenn - the Fenn - competition happened every year, and this particular friend of my father - won the - the - the competition that year, the race. Well - it was long race you see, similar to what they have in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Holland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And - these skates w
ere made from a sword. They were beautiful skates and - I - I lost them when we moved into the flat here unfortunately. But they would be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 They were made from a sword?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Beg your pardon? Yes, made - like - belonged to the sword blade, you know, t
he shaving blades, similar. They were made from a sword. He was a horse trainer, he trained horses eventually went to Rumania and then on to Germany, but he trained the - horses for the - Rumania Royal Family that time, so I prized the - the skates but I 
forgot to gather them up when I moved into the flat here. But skating was quite a - quite a prominent thing then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Great fun?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, the ponds - there were quite a few ponds, lots of them now are done away with but - there was still lots }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 - the - the local - the Marque}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
s of Bute's - Hooe - Luton Hooe used to have a - a yearly - a - a - there used to be competitions there. But there was a com - there was a - a charge made, an admission charge which was given to charity. But that was - that was always a
lmost always on every year. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose} Hooe. To my memory. So whether the - whether the - the ice age was a bit more prominent then I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I think the winters were a bit harder weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were there children that your parents wouldn't let you play with? Did they disapprove of any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Well, no, no, but there's just about one family, just about one family that - we had to fight shy of, the - they were rather - a rough crowd, but generally speaking you mixed in together. As you did at the schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What were this family like then, this rough family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well how do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did they live in your street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes, that's rather queer because - I sometimes see - old friends of mine, one 
is - now eighty-seven, he lived just a - a - above where I lived - the - the streets used to - co-operate together somehow, the - the - the boys and girls in this - street named Tavistock Street - there must have been - not far short of a - a dozen - frie
n
ds who I - I could remember still existed not many years ago, some got killed in the first world war. But we used to mix in together. Competitions together. Football and up and down - down the street with it, 'cos there was no traffic to speak of, and if 
a
 cart came down we used to stop and let it go past and - and that sort of thing happened, there wasn't even cycles to ex - any extent then, because the three wheel hadn't been invented - vented. See one time - the - the bikes in those days, I can remember
 
a girl riding down a - a very steep hill in Luton, and - she - she'd lost - control of the pedals you see, and the brake which operated just on the front wheel - if you put it on too severe over you went. And - so it was a matter of putting it on very - v
e
ry softly, and if you could, drag your feet on the ground if you did get - over powered, but this particular girl I remember she had to put her feet out - and - there was - this steep hill with a - the bottom street - crossing of course, and she went - yo
u knew what was going to happen, she simply went into the wall.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Was she hurt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Oh yes, quite a bit, those things were quite common until the free wheel came in. And then the brakes happened at the back too, do you follow. But the free wheel - I can remember the free wheel coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Oh yes. Oh I biked - I biked with that friend at the bottom, yes, I - I've known him for forty-eight years. I say while he was doing the Bedfordshire fllor we cycled round and round - bu
t I cycled from - it was some time - it wasn't until I was - seventeen that I could afford a bike, then I had to boy a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You didn't have one when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, I had to buy a second - I - I bought the - I bought - the cycle of my boss the
 man who invented the - the straw helmet, and he was the - original captain of the - of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose} - cycle - club. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 Penny farthings}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008  and all sorts of funny sort of bikes you see. Then he organised a trip eventually to - to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St Albans{\*\xmlclose}, and I believe they sent o
ne or two telegrams to say we got there safely. But of course the roads were so rough you see then. Most of - cart tracks, except that they were like - on the - on Wapling Street here before the first world war, very similar. They were terrible then. Unti
l this - the lorries started to come on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you ever go fishing, did you have enough time to do things like going for walks or going fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Walks - I - I didn't go fishing but - tiddler fishing, oh yes, tiddler fishing with a jam jar, oh yes, 
yes, dear, a popular place at Luton was - just out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 side the - the Mar - the Marque}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
s of Bute's - Luton Hooe, there was a pond there, it was very very popular, and the Luton - Luton - the Lee. The - Lee. Oh yes. Oh that was quite - that was quite popular. I d
idn't have much time though you see, I was - working - at nights you see, Saturdays and Sunday mornings, so it was a matter of - sneaking as best I could - the odd times but it - oh yes, tiddler - tiddler fishing was quite a popular sport, in all the rive
rs and ponds at that time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you take part in any organised sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Only the - only the - only the football eventually, only the football, to do with the churches you see, it was the church - churches that fostered - more than the - non-co
nformist chapels. The churches, lots of them had their football teams. Yes. Only what the - unfortunately there wasn't - there wasn't much - there weren't many facilities for football playing - the proper match games. There were one or two recreation grou
n
ds in those very early days, fields that have been - moors - common land. That were - fairly suitable but they always rough compared with what they are today, 'cos the mechanical - the com - mechanical ways of - of doing pitches and - and that sort of thi
n
g is so much more - convenient aren't they. 'Course it was another game I - oh cricket with - with the - an improvised bat and - most of them were bats - knocked out of pieces of wood by the fathers and the - handle was rounded, and - all sorts of differe
nt types of balls. Oh yes, cricket was another - an improvised game - it was just a boys game. Just a -
