re was a gap, there was a gap even between the - the - the building labourer and the carpenter, follow, and the plasterer and and - the bricklayer. There was a difference. But - it wasn't - it wasn't all - I don't suppose it would be much more pronounced 
t
han it is between the - the highly skilled - toolmaker and the - and the man on the - on the bench, you know, the - the men on the - the - vehicle going round. I don't suppose - you see, even today - a highly skilled worker can - considers himself superio
r - superior in a way doesn't he, even he -
