oesn't mean a thing - at one time a mason - was someone of some - some importance. Because he could afford the yearly - subscription which was something, a good deal, and his regalia and so on, and then he got to be a - he'd got to be voted in - by - by p
eople who - wanted to be a mason, do you follow. So the ordinary sort of - working man was never a mason. Unless it was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}, funny enough in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
