What - what you call - there used to be a - a very famous heart - a heart - tablet, a Brompton heart tablet, there was also a Brompton TB tablet, Brompton lozenges were very famous in those days for TB. Don't think they did much good, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And they had a heart tablet too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. Had a heart tablet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And you had to go all the way there just to collect the tablet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. And - and to be examined you see. By the heart specialist you see. But they couldn't have had - I couldn't have had m}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 rtal disease of the heart other - otherwise I shouldn't have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Do you remember anybody in your district being got out of the district because they were so rough, by the rest of the people living in the area?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well of course I do - I'll tell you what they used - the rough music, you know what that meant don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You tell me what you remember of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Don't think I dare. Rough music was - rough music was of course - the - the wives round the district - taking out the tin pans, the top 
- the - the - any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008  sort of - saucepan lids and be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 gin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 nin}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 g them like that you see, like they do in Ireland, like the - the dustbin lids you see, for a certain - female who was - well she was - well, she was acting different to what she should have done, she w
as having - boyfriends or have another man in do you follow. Oh it was against - it was against immorality, oh - and they - that would happen somewhere towards midnight you see. And the rumour would go round and eventually they'd check up and - and then t
hey would start and they'd get together and rough music would happen. Oh yes, that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did it stop the woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well - I suppose it did but it's rather queer because it was regarded as - funny eventually, I remember that my step-father managed - he -
 he - he managed to work for - a firm whose still a - quite a huge firm now - who eventually - repaired the - Luton Hooe estate when - Sir Julius Werner took it over from the Bute people. But they - they - got a - a big job in London, my - my step-father 
w
as a plumber, decorator and so on and he - he was sent - he was - on this London job, used to come home weekends. And one particular Saturday my mother - have a bit of fun you see, she said, look - there was an alleyway coming up to our house and - he use
d
 to come up this alley from the bottom, you could see him coming up you see - from our - our window which was over the side of the street, and my mother said, now look, I want you to wave your handkerchief - when - your dad - enters the bottom of the alle
y
. So I said, yes, all right. So I didn't know what it meant you see. So eventually this Saturday - afternoon - come up in the alley and I see him come I went like this with the handkerchief I - then I got out of the way. When he got to the house the broom
 was sticking out of the bedroom window. You follow what that means don't you? With - to indi - to say to come in. Just to kid him on. So this sort of thing - those sort of things happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 She had a sense of humour then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 We talked about school last time, did you go to another school after the first one you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. No, not - you'll find - you'll find that in the - you'll find that in the - you'll find that in the - in the book, well it's - in -

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You were transferred to a higher grade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 To a higher grade school. Follow? And - that schoolmaster then took over a new school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What was your higher grade school like, what sort of children were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 It was a - a little improvement on the ordinary elementary board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What age did you go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Eleven. Eleven. So I had two years there you see. Well - ten and a half, had two years so I left school at twelve and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What did you learn there, was it slightly more advanced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Well - it was - it was more advanced on - on - as they used to call then grammar, you follow? Arithmetic - and - they had a woodwork course too. Which was quite good. But it was - but it was an in - it was a more adult - school, an adult -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did girls go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Pardon? No. No. Only boys. The ordinary girls school - and that - that was that, a little attempt in Luton to - to grade the top boys somehow, from the schools into this - Water Street higher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008  }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 grade school. That's cover - that covered the o
ther schools. But not the church school. You see, that - in that - history - that is the church schools and the board schools - but board schools there was that fight you see to get the board schools in existence. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Would you have liked to have stayed on longer for more education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, I would. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You regret not being able to have more do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well of course you see there was schoolmaster, that schoolmaster - I referred to, I - I - we - I was supposed to do a - a - pr
esident of a Friends Adult School many years afterwards, several years, and he was the - he was syllabus secretary and so on and we - we got the - this schoolmaster who still existed, this schoolmaster, the higher grade school, a man named Neville, who wa
s
 also the president of the - PSA, the Pleasant Sunday Afternoon for men, which was then prominent in those days. Quite big - congregations of men Sunday afternoon used to - attend. But - we had him down this - this - schoolmaster Mr Middle, we had him dow
n
 to talk to us one - one evening, many years afterwards and - when - when I explained that I'd been one of his boys he was most interested. But - my friend John Downey's asking - had he - had he ever had a boy of extreme intelligence. He said, yes. One re
m
arkable boy, he says, as a matter of fact his intelligence was - really - en masse. He said, on equal, he says, I - I would say that it - it was - more - it was - superior to any of the schoolmasters, including myself. He could be-t us in this three - add
ing up three ways, the three - three systems you know, when up - running up the - the three - three tables together and arrive at the - the three totals at the top into one, and he could do it quicker than any of the masters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You started work full time at twelve and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Twelve and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Can you just tell me about your first job, what it was like starting full time
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 The first job I started was in the hat trade. And - 1901. That was taking orders around from the - main warehouse, wh
ich is in the main street - to the - the manufacturers the many many manufacturers around the district, do you follow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Walked. Oh yes, walked. But of course the - the - the manufacturers in those days - were - situated - they - t
hey were simply - making hats in - little houses, with tiny factories at the back, follow. Just terrace houses, they still exist in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
. And - they had - just - they'd have the - the wife and perhaps another one or two, sewing hats, and the men would blo
ck them, what we call block them with an iron, do you follow, stiffen them and block them into the shape. And then they're taken down to the warehouses in the main street and sell the hats at so much - best - best price they could get, that was how it was
 done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And your job was to take the orders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Take the - take the orders round well oftentimes of course in the busy seasons I was - I start work at half past eight in the morning, there was an hour for lunch. No tea time, or at least I don't remem
ber - there was some little - tea break or some little break in the factory, but there was no - definite teatime.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Would you go home for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, which wasn't very far away. And then - we worked on - until - of times nine o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What was your wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Six shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were you pleased with that at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Yes. That went on - there was a shilling rise per year if you deserved it. Well, you worked on Saturdays until - in the busy time you worked 'til six o'clock on the Saturday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You never go any more for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Oh no. No. But then there was - but then - the dull season, there was a dull season - now making the straw hats - was - was a very big rush, for the summer season. And then there'd be
 a dull time and there wouldn't be so much work, and then it would come on again - somewhere about October. But - the dull time of course the - you'd get more time off but there was - cleaning up in the factories and the warehouses, all sorts of jobs doin
g to get the place right for the next season. Follow? So - it was a - a matter - it was a usual - usual thing was a - a sixty hour week. I only see Tolstoy this last week talking about the seven - seventy-two hour week they used to work in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Russia{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Well sixt
y hours a week in the - in the building trade was quite usual. The - John Downey started as an apprentice - at Hayward Tylers, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
 and he worked sixty hours - six in the morning 'til six in the evening, Saturdays you see. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What about your employer, do you remember him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Was he a good man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Well - no, he's rather queer type, he - he started in the same way that I did as an order boy some very many many years before. But he was a very - rather queer because - he could hand
 - he could write with his left hand but not his right, he was a left handed writer, but - his - his left hand writing was - intolerable. Simply - simply - strokes. Now - there was no curves at all, he simply got his letters - by strokes somehow. But he w
as a man regarded in the town as - quite a - a - quite a clever man, it was the biggest warehouse in the town too. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Was he good to his employees, was he good to the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, reasonably - well there was - rather queer - because the - the
 insurance scheme that - the first insurance scheme came into being - somewhere about that time, nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 pence for four}{\rtlch\fcs1 
