e first old age pension scheme was brought forward by the Liberal party. And - the Conservatives - eleven voted against it and all the others abstained. First old age pension scheme, time of Lloyd George's government, Asquith, well in this }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008  nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
pence for four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 pence scheme came in, what was called the nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 pence for four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid415648\charrsid3227008  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
pence - and - that meant that people has got to have a card, a star card, sort of. In a similar way to what it is now. And the - the brother - the brother of the - Grafter, this warehouse 
where I worked was the sort of head accountant, or supposed to have been. But he was responsible for this card system, and he committed suicide through it. Yes, so it was rather queer, yes, he committed suicide. So it's rather strange. But - the - but thi
s
 boss himself became - he was quite a famous man. There was also famous buyers that used to come down - and were regarded as tremendously important people. At that time we were - we were - war with the Boers, and - the mothers used to frighten the childre
n
 saying that old Kruger will have you. Kruger was the Boer, the boss of the Boer - the - the - the - the Boer Republic you see, well we were fighting Krug - Kruger, and - he was a - supposed to have been a terrible man so - used to frighten us with - Krug
e
r, or frighten the small children. And - at that time of course - it was quite - quite a prominent thing that that - in the - in those early days of the hat trade there was certain fears - used to frighten us with different things in the hat factories. Th
e
re - there were certain things they used to do - they'd - set you on hot sponges in the factories, get up - they used to - you - very large sponges, quite as big as - about - as big as your machine there. Fill it full of barley water and put it on a bench
 and - and - if you - got up to anything - that was corporal punishment in a factory. And somebody get hold of you - yes, sit you on a hot sponge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 The adults as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well - the young boys, the boys, yes. To - to discipline us you see. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Was there any kind of trade unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Or a movement of any sort in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 There was no - no trades unions - to any extent, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did the workers get together at all in the hat trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 As a matter of fact - as a matter of fa
ct - up to the last - world war - during the - during this last world war the manufacturers, rather queer, that the manufacturers and I - of course I represented the firm where I was - I was managing, I went to a very large meeting where the manufacturers
 
wanted to get a union. There was a union in the - in the hat trade up in - in - the felt hat trade up in Stockport, man named Worthington came down to - tell us all about it, we wanted to get the - the workers to become - become trade unionists. So that w
e knew what wage we all were paying for certain types of work. But they wouldn't co-operate, weren't interested. So it's never come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Never has been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No. Not - not in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What about at home when you started full time work, did your mother treat you any differently, were you suddenly grown up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Not really, she - she - she was very fond of me 'cos I was the only one left of the first family. No, she - we were still - we were still disciplined. Even almost to the time I got married, I - I 
- I used to be - pretty careful what I said. It's rather queer. My mother was - which - would you like another cup? Pardon? Did you want one? Well the - the same with the schools. There's no doubt that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Because you were a worker and bringing in the money, you gave the money to your mother I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 She didn't treat you any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How about your free time then, did you do anything different then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well when I - it's rather queer that - in my particular - ci
rcumstances - the - you see, my mother then had married - and there were - my - half sisters - were coming - along, follow? And it oftentimes seems to me that - seemed to me that - my spare time was spent - in looking after them. And as soon as I got one 
of me hands another one suddenly arrived. Rather - rather strange, but - I used to - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you go out in the evenings at all with your friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I used to to the church - to the church parish room, that was - and I had some very nice - boyfrien
ds nearby, one - one was quite - became quite a famous man. He was a cripple, and he belonged to the school then we - we collect - the school collected and brought him a donkey and cart - he was paralyzed all down one side, Bill Edward's - mum would remem
b
er, and - he started this donkey and cart - I was - a friend obviously until - 'til he died, he became Luton - the Mayor of Luton eventually, 'cos he - come around how, he became - he used to go around with the - greengrocery, greengrocery - do the greeng
r
ocery trade plus do a little removal, his mother was a widow and - and eventually she turned her little front room into a shop you see, and then - she had - two other - he had a brother and a sister, but - he - got on again - he used to sell programmes at
 
the football match, then he became - when the first cinema came in Luton, he be - sort of - attendant, putting people to their places and that sort of business. And he gradually worked up until - he became - he became the - the - the highest - he came - m
ost important removal man in Luton, became mayor of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}, so that was rather queer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What would you boys have done in the Evenings when you went out? Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well, of course, there was - rather queer, in those young days - the - there w
as what we called the monkey parade. And I suppose it's happened in lots and lots of places more or less in the towns, where the chief parade town - road - road - was where the young people used to walk up and down and team off together. The monkey parade
.
 That - that was - that was - - the Bedford Road was the monkey parade, especially on Sundays after - after chapel and church, in the best clothes, used to - pair off eventually, and - that was quite - that's quite a - that was a quite a prominent thing t
o do, the monkey - monkey par}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 des, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How about girl friends, what age were you when you were allowed to have girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well - not very early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did your mother mind about girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, the first one - the first one I had - tur
ned me down because she - she - she got an idea I - I - I was told afterwards she'd got an idea I was going to die in a year or two's time and it would be a waste of time, that time I was due to die from my heart trouble. But of course she - she married a
 
friend of my wife's - and - and - she had seven children and she died from tuberculosis, so - so she - she - if she'd have had me instead - she was a sweet little girl too, but then that - that was when she was - that was - she was - then - that was about
 fifteen stages.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What was your mother's attitude to girl friends, did she mind you bringing them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
She was - she was rather - my rather - my mother was rather jealous in those early stages of being friendly with - other boys when I used to g
o into their homes rather than - be at home with her. So - it might have been a - her regard - and of course up to the time she died she used to - tend to favour me a little bit with - because I was the son of her first husband you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 She was especially fond of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were you allowed to bring friends home, was there a tradition of bringing friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes. Oh that was universal. Yes. Yes. Going in each others house - peoples homes, oh yes. Well it - it - they was more intima
te, the houses were more or less - nearly all terraced houses, and you found that in terraced houses more, people going in and out, up the same passage, we'd go around to two or three houses at the back you follow, and you would congregate so - so much mo
re naturally together. You'd be forced more or less into - into company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have a bit more money to spend when you started work? Were you able to buy a bit more for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 A little bit - little bit, it's rather queer - we had - a - this 
- this firm I worked for, there's two order - we two order boys, we used to share - the town. The main thorough fare of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
 was divided. He delivered the orders to one side of - that main thoroughfare, and I delivered the orders to all - all the others y
ou see in the other - other part and - and we used to meet - meet together after you finished in the afternoon and - walk back to the warehouse and so on. The immediate - our immediate superior was a - a fellow of about two years our senior. Who - was the
 eldest of a - of a family - a widowed mother - and they were in very strait circumstances but he was a - he was also - very prominent in the - main Baptist - church at that time. Quite a clever fellow too, he became quite a - quite a prominent man in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
 eventually, but - we used to in those days - used to - get Christmas boxes from the manufacturers. They all give - give us about sixpence or a shilling each you see, each Christmas. And we used to pool this money together, and previous to we two boys goi
n
g there this - this overseer - 'cos one of the order boys - and - and it was customary for the two order boys to give the money in to this - the - overseer and - so the three divided the money. And we carried on the good work but suddenly - we two decided
,
 well we did the work, he does - he doesn't - he doesn't do any orders at all, why should he have the money, so - we put it to him, well you don't do anything to do with this, the Christmas boxes are ours, so we are having them this Christmas. And after c
o
nsidering - in his Christian sort of way he said, well yes - yes, maybe you're right. We didn't realize that - he was relying on - this money to help through Christmas. Then - somehow he got reported to us in some way, we decided to give him a fifth and w
e're having two fifths each. And he seemed to be very thankful about that but of course we relented afterwards and we gave him a third. That's how - that's how the times were, that a few shillings meant a lot. And of course - sorry,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008  well you see - the - the insta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
lment system and the - the - the people had lots of things - on the tick as they called it then. And suits - I used to have my suits, a fifty shilling suit used to be a shilling a week you see, that used to make nearly a year to pay for that suit. Th
at used to come about Easter time. So - all those sort of things you see - you didn't have much money - to spare.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. At - at the age of sixteen I joined the Liberal party, mind - mind - let's be fair, I j
oined the Liberal party - because - draughts - draughts and chess, draughts chiefly, there were draught clubs. Yes. And these clubs - rather queer, the - the Liberal draught club was quite a club and I became quite clever at draughts, before - before I wa
s sixteen. Oh yes, that was another - that was another pastime. And I joined this draught club and I became one - one of the top players, I remember we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bedford
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} once and I tied - with a schoolmaster, which was quite an achievement. Then - draughts we
nt off somehow and chess - replaced it. Then of course there was snooker that - that came, snooker in the - in the - in the clubs, snooker and billiards, that became a bit - more - affluent you see and this is - with the - people - joining these - these p
olitical clubs. The clubs became quite a thing. The Lib - the Liberal and - and Conservative clubs were the two main clubs in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose}
. And of course the Labour hadn't emerged you see, I can remember Kier Hardy, the first four getting into Parliament and they - they were sort of the - the under - the underdogs of the Liberal party, they were - nurtured by the Liberal party. So that -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You didn't work for politics at all did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes, I canvassed, yes, I canvassed for quite a few and I - I - I - not
 - not - not Parliamentary - meetings but I - I took the - chair at some of the - ward meetings, to do with the Liberal party, and eventually the - Conservative party. Nearly said the Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 It's a bit like you and your churches?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's 
right, yes, and so - that - that's rather - of course during - during this last war you could belong to all three parties, which I did. We were all fighting the same enemy anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What year were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What year was it? 1915. Early 1915. The spring of 1915. Easter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How long had you known your wife when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How long had I - known my wife, seven years. I had done. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 By a little trip at - to Bedford with a friend of mine, and - we were in
 a boat, this friend and my - and myself, and - my wife then - with her friend was walking down the prom and - we - we met in that way, and then came home to Luton, together, and from then on - my wife and I - came together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 She lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton{\*\xmlclose} did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes, she - she was born -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And you met her in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bedford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, I met her in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bedford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Yes, rather queer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How far away did she live from you in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 About - oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 quarters of a mile. Not far, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember her moving at all, did her family moved around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 From where she was? Oh yes, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Never out of the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh no. No. They moved into a new home - another part of the district up this way, and - so each night I used to - leave her and the
n walk home which was quite a - reasonable distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember the first time you met her parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, that was in the first home she lived in - a Street called {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Wenlock Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Oh yes, I met - met her - people, they were - very - very - strict Methodists, the whole of her family. And I was high church you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You've been everything in your time haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's right, so eventually when - when we got married we - as she was in the low church district the banns were read the
re so - we were married at a low church, was the compromise between - the high church and the Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 When you say a low church district, did it go in districts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh but the pat - no, in parishes you see. Only this particular church is high church was the - the ritualistic 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}church{\*\xmlclose} of Luton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That was when you went to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, that's right. She went to Methodist - Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What did they think about you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh they accepted me. Yes, yes. But though - as - as a matter of fa
ct - as a matter of fact now this - did I tell you - show you this? No? That was my - mother-in-law's wedding ring, that must be nearly a hundred years old. And when she died - I put it on my finger and they said, oh you'd better have the ring, I said, an
yway I'm the only male that could - wear it, I've never met a male since that could wear it on the proper finger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 It's quite small isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. It's rather queer. Although - very charming, she was a sweet woman. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember the first time you went to their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Can you describe it to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Oh yes - one - one Sunday afternoon - I went - I went to - a - I went to her home, rather queer, because her - her cousin - was on a visit from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Yarmouth{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Very - large - nice looking girl but rather strong, she was an athlete again. And - during the afternoon - in playing around - all of us in the - in the di}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 ing - in the lounge or the front room as they used to call them - she hit me across the head - ear quite - playfully, and burst the drum. She didn't know anything about it and never did, but it meant me - ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 ing doctor's treatment in the town here, and the treatment was wrong, and eventually I had to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Golden Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} hospital in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose} - and they said - well of course it was damaged by the Luton - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}
}Luton{\*\xmlclose} doctor. The - the - the treatment was too fierce, you see, otherwise it would have healed up quite naturally. So I remember that particular day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember being shy when you met them, or had you known them at all before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Only a little. The sister and the brother, she had a sister and a brother, so I knew those - those two slightly but - hadn't met the parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember being shy about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I don't think so particularly, I had 
moved around quite a bit with - activities in the church so I - I wasn't a shy individual. So I got on along very nicely with her people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did they ask you questions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did they want to know about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes, they wanted to kno
w about my family, discreet questions, and my mother too, my mother wanted to know - because I - I took my - I took my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 fianc\'e9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
 home, and - she was accepted there and - we got on very well with regard to family contacts, very nicely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How soon did you decide to get married after you'd met her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Took seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Seven years before you got engaged you mean, did you get engaged as such?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. Still got the engagement ring, it's rather - excuse me, it's rather queer - this might interest you q
uite slightly. Took it off - to the day she got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Eighteen months before you got engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. Now - see I can - I can - wear that too, that's rather queer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you buy that for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 'Course - yes, they're very - they're very modest, in the region of about twenty-five shillings was as much as one could afford. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were you just going out together for seven years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Without going out with any other boy or girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh no. On we - absolutely - it was recognized in those days more or less - too keep to the - the - the party one, follow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Had you had any girl friends before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes. They all turned me down really. But of course - rather queer. No, I - apart from one. I wasn't too - I wasn't too m
uch in love with her and - and her friend who became quite a big boot - merchant in the town - long since dead, but his wife - is still alive, and - we - in those days there used to be dances all organized - many dances. This - young fellow, this - friend
 of mine - seemed to take to this - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 fianc\'e9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
 of mine and - so I - sort of - got them together and they eventually married. So I got hold of - I got off that responsibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You weren't too keen anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How about your wife had she had other boyfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes, she had - she had about two boyfriends before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How old were you when you first met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Eighteen. Eighteen - nine - eighteen or nine - no, about - I was married in 1912 - I was married after - when I was twenty-s
ix, yes, about eighteen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Why did you wait so long before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Saving up for marriage. You see, it was customary then you see these days the - the parent - the parents of the girl - have to foot the bill for the marriage. Living 
up with the Jones's. There's the - church invariably, the church vows and then there's the choir, the reception afterwards. There the conveyances backwards and forwards which means - and the - of course the drink bill and the reception plus all the rest o
f it, means - an outlay of - two or three hundred pounds or more.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
But, you see, in those days that did not happen. You see - parents are responsible more or less today, but then, no, you see - in those early days, I'm talk
ing about pre-1914 especially - family life was - well, the - the children - were responsible - for - their parents as they got old. You see, even if they went - even if they went to the - what was called the work house or the union, the children had to -
 
contribute a certain amount of money towards their upkeep. But most times the - the children - accepted the responsibility of looking after parents in the old age. Parents weren't able to - to save enough to look after themselves in old age. So it was the
 children - invariably, who - who had that responsibility, it's completely changed now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 When you say you saved up to get married, what were you saving for, were you saving for the wedding or for setting up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Wedding, no, a wedding was nothi
ng. No, we - we - we were - we were married I - I had - we certainly - there were one or two taxis in Luton, only one or two, and I engaged one taxi to take our small party to the church - and then after the reception, which was just a little tea -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How many came to the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh about - eight or nine, not more, that was customary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were they relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, relations, the next door neighbour, we were very - neighbours and we were very very friendly with. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 They were her relations, your relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 nd - oh yes, in my - my - above}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008  - yes - there might have been a - there might have been - twelve, I doubt it though. But there were - so I had my - my mother and father, my step-father didn't go but we - we celebrated in other ways you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 They didn't come to your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
NO, just - they came to the wedding but they - then they went home you see, we just had a small - I believe my - I believe my - sisters came, yes, they did that's right, my sisters came. Then after
 - after the tea party - my wife and I had arranged with a - arranged to go to - West - Westcliffe, that's near Southend, for just the - Easter - holiday, 'cos holidays weren't paid - you see, those holidays in those days there was just Whitsun holiday, t
wo - two days for - one day for Easter, people worked on Good Friday, so they -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 So you got married on Easter Saturday did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Easter Saturday, that's right. And we had the - there was still hansom cabs, with a horse, hansom cab to take us from 
- my wife's - home to the railway station, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And then you caught a train to Westcliffe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And your mother and father didn't come to the reception?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 They went to the - they went to the wedding but they didn't come to the reception, my two sisters came, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Why was that, did they not want to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Oh - no, just the matter of - perhaps - I don't know, things happen - more or less like that, my mother had lots of look - to look after at home I suppose. So - but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What was her father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Beg your pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What was your wife's father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 He was a blocker - a straw hat blocker in the hat trade. As my father had been - in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Was her home much the same sort of home as yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Just about he same. Although they had moved into a new - their - their home was a - a newly built home, only a year or two, they went into the new home, follow. But you see homes in those days - hadn't altered much with regard to rent. People didn't b
uy their own homes, they couldn't, not in those days, not the ordinary sort of working class people. And of course there were no council houses, as perhaps you are aware of, no council houses. And the - the houses were put up by in - for investment, small
 
or larger - landlords who - just - gathered the rent you see, and - there were always seemed - for instance, getting a house was no trouble. I didn't worry about a house, getting a house. I - I - I had almost a new house, a friend of mine had been married
 
about a year before and he was - he was - he - he got a job at - at the Grey and White works which was at - one of the early aeroplane works at Hendon, long before Hendon became any air - airplane district, there was just this one Grey and White Works, Gr
e
y and White was a big - airman in the first world war, follow. Well I remember all the history of those airplane exploits, and he - he got a job, Hendon at that time was just a countryside you see, and he got a new home at - Hounslow which was very near. 
So we used to go up and see him occasionally, but we moved into his house. Just as -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Housing wasn't short then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Pardon? Oh no, no trouble at all. And the queer part about it - when you - when you - you realize about inflation now - you see, the 
rents of terraced houses and of course terraced houses were - the main housing - conditions - of sixty or seventy years ago, going back. They - your houses put up, two bedrooms, three bedrooms, and the rents would be in the region of five shillings to six
 and six, seven shillings according to the amount of bedrooms. Well now five shillings was - the - the rent my mother was paying before the end of the last century, five shillings. For two bed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 roomed house, a nice home, but a terrace home, nice garden at th
e back, but you see now - I got married in 1915, and I - got a - a better, newer home - only two bedrooms - but with a nice garden at the back and a front - little front garden, plus by win - a win - bay window which gave it a little bit of superiority, a
n
d that was seven shillings. Now that was some - that was somewhere about twenty years afterwards at least you see. So rents did not alter very much, and that - that rent went on until they became controlled, and when I moved out I was paying about eleven 
or twelve shillings - in 1938. You follow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How about furnishing your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Well you had - that - that was the point, in courtship - in courtship I think you - if you - if you - make enquiries you'll find that - courtship meant this. With the sinc
ere - courting couples - the man or the - the male - managed to get as much money to furnish the house and the girl - the bottom drawer provided the house linen. See? The bottom drawer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Your wife had a bottom drawer did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. That meant all 
the - the - the bottom drawer meant that she got all the linen and the pillow cases, the sheets, the table cloths and what have you, all those sort of things, she was more or less responsible for. There might have been a few presents, always were, but not
 
often - not of a - of an elaborate type you see, like you - these - these days you see there's - there's a long list of presents you see, a long list isn't there. And you choose them look down you see, well that's - that's procedure these days so everythi
ng's done to help the courting couple.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You did it all yourself in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Absolutely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have many presents at your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No. No, I don't suppose I had more than half a dozen altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You didn't have them set out for people to see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
No, simply gave - my mother gave me a fender you see in those days the houses you - you take - the - 'course there were no bathrooms of course - a top bathroom was not back - it was unknown, it was - it was not a prac - a practical 
proposition in the first place. Up until - up to the - first world war nearly all the houses had still got - the fire, with the oven one side, and the boiler - the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What was the fender for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 The fender was just - it was a wide - it's a
 - it was a wide - a - hearth, with a fender - to dry things on, or - or a fender - a steel fender which you cleaned with brick dust, brick dust which you cleaned knives too with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 This is what your mother gave you for your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 This was - th
e fender you see. And then of course the - the grates were - were shone with - with this - sort of oven - black - polish, and they used to look very beautiful. The little brass tap for the - for the water, then you see - in those days - yes, there - there
 was a boiler one side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And you could take hot water from it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, that was what it was for.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008  You cooked one side in the ove}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 n, and you usually kept filling up with water so you had hot water. You see there was no - no - there was no gas stoves. An
d of course electricity hadn't - wasn't known hardly. Follow? As a matter of fact I - I moved into this flat twenty years ago and my house that I came from which was quite a decent place hadn't got electricity. I'd still got gas inca - incandescent gas li
g
hting. Well you see, in those days - the bath - had to be - the water had to be boiled either from the fire or the more - new fangled idea of boiling water on a gas stove, and then a portable bath - conveniently somewhere near where the wa - hot water cou
ld be supplied into, then af - after finishing would be cleaned out and put on one - upside you see, in a convenient place and that was that. But up - upstairs, well of course it would be hopeless. In places -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 So a fender was really a quite important thing for you to have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember any other presents you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, there - rather - yes, it's rather, I - I - it's rather queer, excuse me - quite a - modest you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 But you got some ornamental as well as useful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 When you were courting did you go and see her parents quite a lot, were you in and out of their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes. Oh yes, always. As a matter of fact, it's rather queer that - I used to oftentimes go to chapel with them of a Sund
ay evening. Instead of going to my church which I went to in the morning, I used to go to their chapel in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were you treated as one of the family always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, absolutely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Not as a guest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 One of the family. My - my mother and father too, my step-father, my wife was always - part of the family. I think that was general.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did your two sets of parents get together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Hardly ever. Hardly ever. No, they - that wasn't - you see they were too busy in those days. You see, a m
an worked sixty hours a week invariably - and - the mother - you see, my mother - had eight children, and - so - I know that they - the four - four - four died but - there were lots of responsibilities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 When you were courting was there much in the way of chaperoning, did they allow you to be together by yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
It's rather queer, now - oh yes, yes, they allowed us but you see - my - my wife's father was a very strict man with regard to getting in at night time. Even - on the point of getting 
married, we daren't stop out after ten. And we kept religiously to it. You see, I always used to say, now come on, we must run. So - we - I always kept round the right side of the dear old boy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 But you were allowed out together by yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And left in a room by yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Although they - they - they liked - they liked Sunday to be observed, for instance - I - we buy - we buy - we bought cycles, I used to - we used to cycle tremendously, we used to - we used to cycl
e to Toaster you see. Many times. And - they - they knew of my cousin there, at Brisenorton - but - we hardly dared cycle on a Sunday. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That would have offended her father would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's right, yes. Sunday was observed very much more - w
ell it was. I mean Sunday school then - hardly any - child - it was very rare for a child not to - to go to some Sunday school of some sort or another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you get on well with your parents-in-law after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you go on seeing them quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 We - we used to see them - very very frequently, we used to go to her mother's and - to my mother, yes. Right up to the time they died.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 When her parents were getting old did you help in the house and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I
n a financial side - of - we helped - yes. Well it's rather queer that - my wife's mother died and then - her father - moved - in with her sister. And the sister's husband, into their home. And my - my youngster - my boy up there, he'd come along and he w
a
s then about two, and I used to - help the old boy - a little bit with regard to - the shillings and so on, and I used to give him a half a crown a week - for his tobacco. His - for his tobacco. And it wasn't until after he died that I found he kept all t
hose half shillings in a - in a tin box and - left 'em to my boy - my boy. Rather queer isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 He must have been a nice man, I don't suppose you ever went drinking did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What did you call them before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What do you mean, with regard to the names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you call them Mr and Mrs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Well - I used to call - I used to call my wife's - mother, mum, yes I - yes I used to call her mum - before we were married. But - I avoided calling her father dad. So we managed to get along - without names, in some way. His -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Even after you were married you didn't call him dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, I never remember calling him dad, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You didn't call him his Christian name or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I - I forget now what his Christian name was, oh, Ben, that's right, Ben, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 But you didn't call him that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
No. No. But I think the family - I think the courting - days and so on - were more - somehow - personal with regard to family ties. Granted the families we
re larger. The money was - more scarce, the way of enjoying - there was not the television, radio and so on so - you - you got together more and enjoyed yourselves more, in the majority of cases, it didn't happen always. But it did used to - to happen - w
ith the churches and chapels too, nearly everyone went to some sort of - church or chapel, mixing in the social groups so all that - all that helped with regard to family ties didn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Can you remember the first time you took your wife home to meet your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Yes - 'course it was my step-father, it wasn't my own father. And - yes, he - he was - he was very very - so was my mother, but he was extraordinary friendly, it's rather queer - mind you - I was the only one - I was the only one left of
 the previous family, so it was rather unusual for a step-father, to treat a step-child as his own child which he did right up to - the time he died. But - oh yes, they took to my wife - they took to my - yes. And I - I - I should think that would be gene
ral, you can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
I remember you saying that your mother was quite a dominant person and she had a very strong influence on you, she didn't mind about you having a girl friend or getting engaged or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, she didn't, it's rather queer, and
 I was the eldest one, but mind you I kept - I'd kept - at home until - my two younger sisters had become established in the hat trade. And by the time I got married they were earning reasonable money. So much so that a piano had got into the house and th
ey were learning to play the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 So your mother didn't need your money so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
So that she didn't need it so much, not towards the last two or three years, so - but up until that time - one would consider - you see, in those days - those days
, at least two thirds of one's salary went - to help for the board and lodging. You see, I remember - I remember when I was earning - when I was sixteen I was earning - sixteen shillings a week. Well I was paying twelve shillings for board. Didn't allow y
ou much did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember when you were cour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 ing if you were warned off certain things or they tried to discourage you from getting married at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, not the slightest. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Your parents didn't know each other before you started courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Can you describe how often you would have seen your wife when you were courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Almost every night. Yes. Almost every night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 For seven years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What sort of things did you do together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Well there - t
here were walks. See in those days there wasn't much other to do bar cycle and walk. Those were all out - they were round the - the parks at Luton here, the new parts which were very popular, the Luton Hooe, the - the very large Luton park which perhaps y
o
u noticed at all have you. Well there's the history of that you see, that - that park was a - owned by - the - the people do with the London Brick Company eventually. And - it was put up for sale and - the Corporation was offered it for - sixteen thousand
 
odd but they turned it down, too expensive and two of the councils built - bought it between them, half each, and then eventually coaxed the council to take it over and they sold it to the council at what they gave for it. Sixteen thousand odd, well - wel
l the - the main house - the museum is in the - in the house you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You say you went for cycle rides, quite long cycle rides? Did you ever go on holiday together during your courtship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Only - yes, we used to come - to Brisenorton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 To stay with relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Oftentimes to my cousin at Brisenorton and we - then we - of course we - we made friends with - their - there were the - I don't - I don't know whether the Gui}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 ness family still exists round there but the Gui}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 ness family was a famous
 family - of some stability in the neighbourhood, there was the - Hartingdon, there was the - the Crafton people - who my - cousin's husband used to - decorate and so on. He was also to do with the - the local water works, a queer - concern, so - the - we
 used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 You used to go and stay with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
We used to - go there and stay with my cousin, we - sometimes - later on - the weeks holiday which began to happen. Follow? But we - we had - we used to go to Margate - with - my - my - sist - my wife's sister, used to go to a boarding house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 The three of you together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 That's right. Pardon? That's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Would you have been allowed to go, just the two of you do you think before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, that wouldn't have been customary. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Do you remember the moment when you decided to get married, did you actually propose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Well it took us some time to - well we agreed between ourselves that we - we were - already - we already start - even before we're engaged - 
we'd started to save, follow. And in order to get enough furniture to do - furnish the bedrooms, the kitchen and - the - you see the front room, the lounge as we would call it now - often times - young couples - you see, this - even living up with the Jon
e
s's happened, but when couples got married - those that saved, they - they furnished the front room which was an achievement. Lots - lots of 'em couldn't do that so that room was - sort of - the blinds always closed and son on, 'til such time they could -
 get a piece of line down and a few chairs and gradually build it up, but keep it dark more or less obscured until that time. But it took, me that time to - to get enough money to furnish the house, I've still got some of the furniture now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 So you don't actually remember saying, will you marry me, down on one knee or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, I - it was - sort of - we'd already got together, we knew we would get married - I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have to go and ask permission from your wife's parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I
 remember telling - I remember - telling the sister - Alice a very sweet sister, she died from - she died from diabetic trouble, dropped dead, but she was a very sweet girl, older, and she was the responsible one of the family, the mother - she took over 
t
he responsibilities of the mother. So she was the one I - I told and she said, well - now when you get married I'll take charge of the furniture and I'll see everything's fitted up by the time you get back, which she did. And in two or three days and some
h
ow or another she arranged all the furniture which had come down - you see, and - and of course you see in those days - you didn't buy - you - you paid cash. It was rather - one was ashamed of having things on what they called the tick, you follow. They d
idn't buy on - so much a week. So everything was paid for - by - most of the companies - paid cash. It was a job to get anything other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 So you didn't actually have to ask father's permission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What about your own parents, did you tell them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Well my mother wanted me - my mother was - always more or less urging me - why don't you get married - Gray, my name was Graham so it was Gray you see. Why don't you get married. Be nice for you to get married, there's some nice homes up so and so
 and so and so. So really I - it was - I - she didn't want to get rid of me - 'cos I was the only one left of her - of her - previous husband who she was very fond of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 How about the arrangements for the wedding, did you go to see the vicar or did your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
We - we arranged between ourselves - that the - the wedding was to take place at St - St Matthews Church at which they weren't members. But I was - not in that parish so it was convenient anyway for them to have the bans read there, and - I ar
ranged all the other - all the other part. They arranged the little tea party which didn't cost much anyway. And that was customary you see, there - there weren't these big receptions, couldn't afford it. NO.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you arrange it on Easter Saturday for any particular reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
For Easter? Because - I'd have the two days off - I'd have the - the holiday time off, follow. It would be either Christmas, Easter - August Bank Holiday wasn't known in those days. Only the Bank Holiday Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 If you'd taken a holiday yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Too cost - cost too much. And oftentimes the firm wouldn't tolerate that. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have any argument about what sort of a wedding you should have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No. No, it was quite amicable, it was simple. She had her simple - dress, there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did she have a white dress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 There was my wife's sister, there were my - my - wife's brother's wife, and my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Were they bridesmaids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have bridesmaids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Just the two bridesmaids. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 And your wife wore a white dress did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
No. No. It was a cream embroidered - dress - it was cream, would you - you wouldn't term that white would you? Cream, then she changed into a costume when we - when the - by the time the hansom called for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What did you wear, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 The lounge sort. Moss Brothers - hadn't existed at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you have a buttonhole?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes, always buttonholes. You - you said the buttonhole? Well of course buttonholes were customary a
lways. You see, the - little - buttonhole in the coat which still exists doesn't it, only it's stitched up these days, you can't used it, but it's still there, which is silly. But - almost everyone wore buttonholes - Sundays and so on. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did your wife carry flowers, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
I don't know. No. No. No. Although the - the sprays did used to happen. But it's rather queer, now - we got a strict Baptist lady upstairs, no flowers allowed in the strict Baptist chapels at all, as perhaps you
 know. No flowers allowed at the - no wreaths at the funerals. Well now the Methodists they - they varied a bit. Flowers weren't very customary even at the Annivers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 ries. No. It's rather - it was rather strange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 It was quite a small wedding, did you invite people by word of mouth or did you send cards out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh only word of mouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did anyone come from a long way away to come to the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 They were all local were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No. No. It was just a little family wedding, which -
 that was the customary business. Cards - in those days - weren't used by ordinary sort of working class people, and we - and we were working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you do anything the last week before you were married, a stag party or anything with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
Oh yes. Yes, I had a stag - I - yes, I had a little stag party. They were yes, they were - they were in existence then. But that was a church party. Yes, that was a church party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Just men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Oh yes. But of course it was a nigger troupe you 
see, I remember them - the nigger troupe people, and it was - they were all - all people from the nigger troupe you see, but - oh yes, that - there were - there were little - there were little occasions - just before the wedding when - the fellows - mates
 as they used to call them, chums and so on, got together. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 What about your last day at work before you were married, were you teased do you remember at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, there was - there was - yes, there was - rather you see - I worked - I work
ed in a warehouse making the straw helmets and so on for police, and - there were - there was a - quite a - yes, quite a lot of fun, more so I think than you get - you would get today. Those occasions were occasions for fun, helping to make the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 social}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008  - happenings you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Did you see your wife on her wedding day before the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Yes, because we went together. Yes. We went together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Was that unusual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 I'm sorry. No. We went - I - no - the best man and myself went to the church f
irst, that's right, yes. And they followed almost immediately afterwards, that's right, yes. But we walked. We walked. Yes, that's quite true, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 She came in a car?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 She came after, yes, in the - in the car.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Who gave y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12780690\charrsid3227008 ou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 
 away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Her - her brother. Her brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Not her father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 Was there any reason for that?
