I don't know the origin that - the white - the white - the white of course - was to do with - a French - the French - one of the French Emperor's wives what it - the French -
 came - that originated from France. Studying up fashions and all that one gets to know all those sort of things you see. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 But why they separated the bride's and the groom's guests you don't know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No, it's always the groom's one side and th
e - and the - the bride's the other isn't it. Right - left and the right, yes. Oh I remember - I remember being on the right. As a matter of fact it's rather queer because - if such a large church and such a small gathering - that I - I suppose in some jo
cular way I showed them into the seats. While - while the - while the bride was waiting to come along, it was only about half a dozen or so, not many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1203760 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 So you were your own usher? Did you have photographs taken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9069422 GL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8460570\charrsid3227008 No.
